#: ../../../reference/distutils_status_migration.rst:4
msgid "Status of ``numpy.distutils`` and migration advice"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/distutils_status_migration.rst:6
msgid ""
"`numpy.distutils` has been deprecated in NumPy ``1.23.0``. It will be "
"removed for Python 3.12; for Python <= 3.11 it will not be removed until 2 "
"years after the Python 3.12 release (Oct 2025)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/distutils_status_migration.rst:13
msgid ""
"``numpy.distutils`` is only tested with ``setuptools < 60.0``, newer "
"versions may break. See :ref:`numpy-setuptools-interaction` for details."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/distutils_status_migration.rst:18
msgid "Migration advice"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/distutils_status_migration.rst:20
msgid ""
"There are several build systems which are good options to migrate to. "
"Assuming you have compiled code in your package (if not, you have several "
"good options, e.g. the build backends offered by Poetry, Hatch or PDM) and "
"you want to be using a well-designed, modern and reliable build system, we "
"recommend:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/distutils_status_migration.rst:25
msgid "Meson_, and the meson-python_ build backend"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/distutils_status_migration.rst:26
msgid "CMake_, and the scikit-build-core_ build backend"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/distutils_status_migration.rst:28
msgid ""
"If you have modest needs (only simple Cython/C extensions; no need for "
"Fortran, BLAS/LAPACK, nested ``setup.py`` files, or other features of "
"``numpy.distutils``) and have been happy with ``numpy.distutils`` so far, "
"you can also consider switching to ``setuptools``. Note that most "
"functionality of ``numpy.distutils`` is unlikely to be ported to "
"``setuptools``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/distutils_status_migration.rst:35
msgid "Moving to Meson"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/distutils_status_migration.rst:37
msgid ""
"SciPy has moved to Meson and meson-python for its 1.9.0 release. During this "
"process, remaining issues with Meson's Python support and feature parity "
"with ``numpy.distutils`` were resolved. *Note: parity means a large superset "
"(because Meson is a good general-purpose build system); only a few BLAS/"
"LAPACK library selection niceties are missing*. SciPy uses almost all "
"functionality that ``numpy.distutils`` offers, so if SciPy has successfully "
"made a release with Meson as the build system, there should be no blockers "
"left to migrate, and SciPy will be a good reference for other packages who "
"are migrating. For more details about the SciPy migration, see:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/distutils_status_migration.rst:47
msgid ""
"`RFC: switch to Meson as a build system <https://github.com/scipy/scipy/"
"issues/13615>`__"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/distutils_status_migration.rst:48
msgid ""
"`Tracking issue for Meson support <https://github.com/rgommers/scipy/"
"issues/22>`__"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/distutils_status_migration.rst:50
msgid "NumPy will migrate to Meson for the 1.26 release."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/distutils_status_migration.rst:54
msgid "Moving to CMake / scikit-build"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/distutils_status_migration.rst:56
msgid ""
"The next generation of scikit-build is called scikit-build-core_. Where the "
"older ``scikit-build`` used ``setuptools`` underneath, the rewrite does not. "
"Like Meson, CMake is a good general-purpose build system."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/distutils_status_migration.rst:62
msgid "Moving to ``setuptools``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/distutils_status_migration.rst:64
msgid ""
"For projects that only use ``numpy.distutils`` for historical reasons, and "
"do not actually use features beyond those that ``setuptools`` also supports, "
"moving to ``setuptools`` is likely the solution which costs the least "
"effort. To assess that, there are the ``numpy.distutils`` features that are "
"*not* present in ``setuptools``:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/distutils_status_migration.rst:70
msgid "Nested ``setup.py`` files"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/distutils_status_migration.rst:71
msgid "Fortran build support"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/distutils_status_migration.rst:72
msgid ""
"BLAS/LAPACK library support (OpenBLAS, MKL, ATLAS, Netlib LAPACK/BLAS, BLIS, "
"64-bit ILP interface, etc.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/distutils_status_migration.rst:73
msgid "Support for a few other scientific libraries, like FFTW and UMFPACK"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/distutils_status_migration.rst:74
msgid "Better MinGW support"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/distutils_status_migration.rst:75
msgid ""
"Per-compiler build flag customization (e.g. `-O3` and `SSE2` flags are "
"default)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/distutils_status_migration.rst:76
msgid ""
"a simple user build config system, see `site.cfg.example <https://github.com/"
"numpy/numpy/blob/master/site.cfg.example>`__"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/distutils_status_migration.rst:77
msgid "SIMD intrinsics support"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/distutils_status_migration.rst:78
msgid ""
"Support for the NumPy-specific ``.src`` templating format for ``.c``/``.h`` "
"files"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/distutils_status_migration.rst:80
msgid ""
"The most widely used feature is nested ``setup.py`` files. This feature may "
"perhaps still be ported to ``setuptools`` in the future (it needs a "
"volunteer though, see `gh-18588 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/"
"issues/18588>`__ for status). Projects only using that feature could move to "
"``setuptools`` after that is done. In case a project uses only a couple of "
"``setup.py`` files, it also could make sense to simply aggregate all the "
"content of those files into a single ``setup.py`` file and then move to "
"``setuptools``. This involves dropping all ``Configuration`` instances, and "
"using ``Extension`` instead. E.g.,::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/distutils_status_migration.rst:90
msgid ""
"from distutils.core import setup\n"
"from distutils.extension import Extension\n"
"setup(name='foobar',\n"
"      version='1.0',\n"
"      ext_modules=[\n"
"          Extension('foopkg.foo', ['foo.c']),\n"
"          Extension('barpkg.bar', ['bar.c']),\n"
"          ],\n"
"      )"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/distutils_status_migration.rst:100
msgid ""
"For more details, see the `setuptools documentation <https://setuptools.pypa."
"io/en/latest/setuptools.html>`__"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/distutils_status_migration.rst:107
msgid "Interaction of ``numpy.distutils`` with ``setuptools``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/distutils_status_migration.rst:109
msgid ""
"It is recommended to use ``setuptools < 60.0``. Newer versions may work, but "
"are not guaranteed to. The reason for this is that ``setuptools`` 60.0 "
"enabled a vendored copy of ``distutils``, including backwards incompatible "
"changes that affect some functionality in ``numpy.distutils``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/distutils_status_migration.rst:114
msgid ""
"If you are using only simple Cython or C extensions with minimal use of "
"``numpy.distutils`` functionality beyond nested ``setup.py`` files (its most "
"popular feature, see :class:`Configuration <numpy.distutils.misc_util."
"Configuration>`), then latest ``setuptools`` is likely to continue working. "
"In case of problems, you can also try ``SETUPTOOLS_USE_DISTUTILS=stdlib`` to "
"avoid the backwards incompatible changes in ``setuptools``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/distutils_status_migration.rst:121
msgid ""
"Whatever you do, it is recommended to put an upper bound on your "
"``setuptools`` build requirement in ``pyproject.toml`` to avoid future "
"breakage - see :ref:`for-downstream-package-authors`."
msgstr ""
